title: Kim Jong Un looks set to meet Vladimir Putin as Russia tries to buy North Korean weapons
description: Kim Jong Un could travel to Russia to meet president Vladimir Putin, according to a US official.

title: 'Unacceptable behaviour': Spanish men's team express solidarity with women after Rubiales kiss
description: The captains of the Spanish men's team have expressed solidarity with the national women's side after what they call "unacceptable behaviour" by the Spain FA head Luis Rubiales.

title: Rumours of Ebola outbreak at Burning Man Festival - here's why they're false
description: The Burning Man festival in Nevada has been dominated by rain, mud baths and videos of Chris Rock and Diplo's escape - but a slightly different picture is emerging online.

title: Five men arrested after British woman reportedly raped in Cyprus
description: Five Israeli men have been arrested in Cyprus after a British woman reported being raped, a police source has said.

title: Eye-patch clad German chancellor 'looking forward to the memes' after jogging injury
description: German Chancellor Olaf Scholz has said he is "excited to see the memes," after posting a picture of himself wearing a black eye patch.

title: 'Violent riot' in Sweden after Koran burning
description: Clashes described by police as a "violent riot" erupted in Sweden's third-largest city after an anti-Islam protester set fire to the Koran.

title: Empty highways, ghost towns, derelict flats: Has China's economy run out of steam?
description: The southern Chinese city of Zunyi is awash with signs the nation's economy is not in good health.

title: Hop to it! India's moon lander shows off with another touchdown
description: Not content with making history by reaching the lunar surface's south pole, India's moon lander has shown off by hopping to a second soft landing.

title: French actor Mathieu Kassovitz 'seriously injured' in motorbike crash
description: The French actor and director Mathieu Kassovitz is in a "worrying" condition after a motorbike crash on Sunday.

title: Chinese President Xi Jinping will not attend G20 summit in India
description: China's President Xi Jinping will not attend the G20 summit in India this week as bilateral relations remain icy between the two countries.

title: Ukraine's defence minister to be replaced - as Zelenskyy believes 'new approaches' are needed
description: Volodymyr Zelenskyy has announced he will replace his defence minister - marking the biggest political shake-up in Ukraine since the start of Russia's invasion in February 2022.
